<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1859" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βίη</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ης</span>, dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βίηφι</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">force, violence</span>, in the latter sense usually pl.,
          sing. <i><span class="en">Od. 23.31</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; βίη καὶ κάρτος,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 4.415</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> οὐκ
            ἲ̄ς οὐδὲ βίη,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 18.4</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ἀρετῇ
            τε βίῃ τε</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.578</span></i>;
          rarely of the mind, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οὐκ ἔστι βίη
          φρεσί</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 3.45</span></i>; often in
          periphrases w. gen. of proper name, or w. adj., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βίη Ἡρᾱκληείη, Αἰνείᾱο βίη</span>, the might of Heracles, i. e.
          the mighty Heracles, etc.; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βίῃ</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">by force, in spite of</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βίῃ
            ἀέκοντος, δ 646</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          1.430</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
